            "id": "e33c57296d7841b59fa1c",
            "questionText": "A construction manager measures the length of a rectangular foundation as $!$10.500\\,m$!$ and the width as $!$5.200\\,m$!$ using a laser distance meter. However, the meter consistently underreads by $!$5\\,mm$!$. Calculate the actual area of the foundation in square metres ($!$m^2$!$) and express your answer with the correct number of significant figures.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
